1 olive oil
1 packet pine nuts
1 packet pork loin steaks
1 ciabatta
1 cucumber
2 tomato
1 bag Cos Lettuce Mix
1 packet romesco sauce
1 bag basil
1 sachet Nan's Special Seasoning
2 packet Italian dressing
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

• Heat frying pan over medium-high heat
• Toast pine nuts, tossing, until golden, 3-4 mins. Transfer to a bowl
• In a separate bowl, combine pork, spice blend and a drizzle of olive oil
• Return frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil. Cook pork, until cooked through, 3-4 mins each side

• Slice ciabatta in half. Toast or grill to your liking, then cut or tear into chunks
• Roughly chop cucumber and tomato

• In a separate bowl, combine cucumber, tomato, ciabatta, lettuce mix and Italian dressing. Season
• Slice pork
• Plate up salad and pork. Top with romesco (add less if desired!)
• Sprinkle with cheese and toasted nuts. Tear over basil to serve